    "methodology": "Uptake is measured as the proportion of eligible people who completed a screening kit within six months of invitation. The programme transitioned from guaiac faecal occult blood test (gFOBt) to faecal immunochemical test (FIT) in June 2019. Age expansion from 60-74 to 50-74 began in April 2021 and is being phased in over several years. Mortality rates are age-standardised to the 2013 European Standard Population. Early stage detection refers to cancers diagnosed at Stage 1 or Stage 2 among screen-detected cases.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "COVID-19 caused screening pauses in 2020, creating an invitation backlog that inflated apparent uptake as paused invitations were re-sent",
      "The switch from gFOBt to FIT in 2019 means pre- and post-2019 uptake figures are not directly comparable",
      "Age expansion is ongoing — uptake among newly eligible younger cohorts is typically lower, which may depress headline rates as expansion completes"
    ]
